text: Baima Tibetan Ethnic Township () is an ethnic township for Tibetan people under the administration of Pingwu County in northern Sichuan province, China. , it has four villages under its administration. == See also == * List of township-level divisions of Sichuan == References == Category:Township-level divisions of Sichuan Category:Pingwu County
title: Baima Tibetan Ethnic Township
